Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 28. Name Archokrates. Perhaps only one other die is known for this month from Archokrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0875)
